1.help: The siteId is a unique number that identifies a manager, player or server in a project. Sites can also be created without assigning them to a specific physical machine. The site id can be found when looking at the Master in the Devices Tab
1.name: siteId

2.help: The deviceId is a per-site unique number that identifies a kind of layer, camera, output or a dmx-device.
2.name: deviceId

3.help: The parameterName is a string that identifies a property of a device. (ASCII only)
3.name: parameterName

4.help: A numeric value to a corresponding parameter.
4.name: parameterValue

5.help: doSilent (when set) prevents the activation of a parameter. It will stay inactive and won't be treated as an active value.
5.name: doSilent

6.help: doDirect (when set) sets the value without using the default value smoothing
6.name: doDirect

7.help: A numeric value to a corresponding parameter.
7.name: parameterValue

8.help: The number of elements in this tuple
8.name: tupleDimension

9.help: The data of the tuple collection
9.name: tupleData

10.help: The parameterName is a string that identifies a property of a device.
10.name: parameterName

11.help: A numeric representation for a parameter. This is faster than using the text based identifier.
11.name: parameterKindId

12.help: A time span in milliseconds that it takes for a parameter to fade to it's new value. A value of 0 means no parameter smoothing
12.name: smoothingTime

13.help: States whether something is currently selected in the master interface
13.name: isSelected

14.help: Number of devices currently in selection.
14.name: selectedDevicesCount

15.help: A index for the collection of selected devices. Get selected devices count with [c:16]
15.name: selectionIndex

16.help: The unique identifier for a sequence. The first/default sequence is 1
16.name: sequenceId

17.help: The HOURS part of a time or timespan
17.name: hours

18.help: The MINUTES part of a time or timespan
18.name: minutes

19.help: The SECONDS part of a time or timespan
19.name: seconds

20.help: The FRAMES part of a time or timespan
20.name: frames

21.help: Resources can have a identifier pair (Folder and File ID) for external control like DMX,Art-net and alike. This is the FOLDER part. The Widget Designer also takes advantage of this kind of addressing of resources.
21.name: dmxFolderId

22.help: Resources can have a identifier pair (Folder and File ID) for external control like DMX,Art-net and alike. This is the FILE part. The dmxFileId identifier is unique in each dmx-folder. The Widget Designer also takes advantage of this kind of addressing of resources.
22.name: dmxFileId

23.help: The bank identifier for presets. They can be found in the Master's interface in the Project tab. The Presets folder contains all banks.
23.name: bankId

24.help: A identifier for a preset. It is unique in each bank.
24.name: presetId

25.help: When forMesh it set, the command executes it's action for the MESH parameter of the given device. When set to false it is executed on the MEDIA parameter.
25.name: forMesh

28.help: A string representing the full path to a resource of the project. Resources in the root folder can be addressed directly like "resource.mpv". The same resource in a subfolder named "sub" can be referenced by "sub/resource.mpv"
28.name: resourcePath

29.help: A path in the project. leave blank for the root folder. Subfolders are separated by a forward slash, no terminating slash is allowed.
29.name: projectPath

30.help: Item IDs are counted from top to bottom in the project tree. Nesting has no influence on counting order. The first item is 0 (always the project root folder)
30.name: itemIdFrom

31.help: Item IDs are counted from top to bottom in the project tree. Nesting has no influence on counting order. The first item is 0 (always the project root folder)
31.name: itemIdTo

32.help: Playback status of a sequence. Possible values are 1 (Play), 2 (Stop) or 3 (Pause)
32.name: transportMode

38.help: When true then the action is done to the NEXT element. When set to false then the action is done to the PREVIOUS element.
38.name: isNext

39.help: A unique identifier for a cue.
39.name: cueId

40.help: The numeric visibility from 0 (totally opaque) to 255 (fully visible)
40.name: transparency

41.help: The mode for the SMTPE link: 0 (None), 1 (Send) or 2 (Receive)
41.name: timeCodeMode

42.help: Determines what should happen when the incoming timecode stops
42.name: stopAction

43.help: A Windows-Styled path to a file. ("C:cooluxcontentsamplevideo.mpv")
43.name: filePath

44.help: A path in the project tab. ("somefolder/otherfolder") Leave empty for root directory.
44.name: projectPath

45.help: TreeItemIDs are counted from top to bottom in the project tree. Nesting has no influence on counting order. The first item is 0 (always the project root folder)
45.name: treeItemIndex

46.help: Resources can have a identifier pair (Folder and File ID) for external control like DMX,Art-net and alike. This is the FOLDER part. The Widget Designer also takes advantage of this kind of addressing of resources.
46.name: dmxFolderId

47.help: Resources can have a identifier pair (Folder and File ID) for external control like DMX,Art-net and alike. This is the FILE part. The dmxFileId identifier is unique in each dmx-folder. The Widget Designer also takes advantage of this kind of addressing of resources.
47.name: dmxFileId

48.help: A Windows-Styled path to a folder. ("C:cooluxcontentsample_folder")
48.name: folderPath

49.help: A Windows-Styled path to a folder. ("C:cooluxcontentsample_folder")
49.name: folderPath

50.help: True: Execute action on all equally named items. False: Do action only for one/the first item having the target name.
50.name: allEquallyNamed

51.help: True: Remove folders. False: Keep folder structure.
51.name: removeFolder

52.help: A Windows-Styled path to a file. ("C:cooluxcontentsamplevideo.mpv")
52.name: filePath

57.help: Convert MPEG color space to full 24bit
57.name: useMpegColorSpace

58.help: Enables the use of the alpha channel
58.name: useAlphaChannel

60.help: A Windows-Styled path to a folder. ("C:cooluxcontentprojectsmyproject")
60.name: folderPathToProject

61.help: The name of the XML file of the project. ("myproject.xml")
61.name: projectXmlFileName

99.help: A string representing the full path to a resource of the project. Resources in the root folder can be addressed directly like "resource.mpv". The same resource in a subfolder named "sub" can be referenced by "sub/resource.mpv"
99.name: resourcePath

129.help: The width of a thumbnail image in pixels. Always comes in pair with [thumbnailHeight]
129.name: thumbnailWidth

130.help: The width of a thumbnail image in pixels. Always comes in pair with [thumbnailWidth]
130.name: thumbnailHeight

131.help: 4 Byte/Pixel encoded image data (BGRA). There is no header, only raw data. The width and height can be found in [thumbnailWidth] and [thumbnailHeight]
131.name: thumbnailData

139.help: A path in the project tab containing media
139.name: sourceProjectPath

145.help: A path in the project to a playlist.
145.name: playlistPath

156.help: The name of a encoding preset. A list of possible presets can be found in the Video Recording Tab
156.name: encodingPresetName

161.help: A string representing the full path to a live input resource of the project. Live Inputs that reside in the root fodler of the project can be addressed directly like "MyLiveInput". The same resource in a subfolder named "sub" can be referenced by "sub/MyLiveInput"
161.name: liveInputResourcePath

174.help: A path in the project to a canvas.
174.name: canvasResourcePath

192.help: The frames per second to be used.
192.name: fps

193.help: True: This text contains formatting that should be applied to the text asset. False: Set the raw text only.
193.name: isFormatted

208.help: A index pointing to a group
208.name: groupIndex

212.help: Set to true to enable automatic DMX IDs. If you want auto DMX IDs, please set any dmxFolderId and dmxFileId to 0 (if this function accepts any)
212.name: autoIncrementDmxId

213.help: The name of the resource without path
213.name: resourceName

214.help: The settings of the video resource
214.name: options

244.help: A Tree item index. This only includes MEDIA
244.name: treeItemsMediaIndex
